  "plainText": "Exclusive to:\nFancy Spiralled Tubers\nFood Info\n37.5\n3\n15\nVeggie\nObject Info\n10 Days\nCan be Burned\n40\nCooking Info\nx1 x1 x2\n15 sec\n10\nMiscellaneous\n\"potatotornado\"\n“Potato, scientifically infused with the power of a tornado!”\n–Wilson\n“Woah, I didn't know potatoes came in that shape!”\n–Willow\n“Wolfgang loves potato.”\n–Wolfgang\n“Spiralling, just like my life.”\n–Wendy\n“HIGH DENSITY FUEL MADE BY MY MINION”\n–WX-78\n“How creative!”\n–Wickerbottom\n“I'll eat a tater in any form.”\n–Woodie\n“What an odd way to serve potatoes.”\n–Maxwell\n“Blech.”\n–Wigfrid\n“Woah! It's cool, AND edible!”\n–Webber\n“Junk food can be as enjoyable as anything gourmet.”\n–Warly\n“Whirly Swirly!”\n–Wormwood\n“Count on Warly's cookin' to always make my day.”\n–Winona\n“I think I remember when I used to eat food. Maybe.”\n–Wortox\n“Hee-hee, spinny potato!”\n–Wurt\n“I usually mash my potatoes.”\n–Walter\n“Time is kind of like a swirly potato.”\n–Wanda\nFancy Spiralled Tubers are Vegetable Food Items exclusive to Don't Starve Together. They are cooked in the Crock Pot by combining 1 Potato, Twigs and two fillers. It takes 15 seconds to cook.\nAdding Meats will result in Kabobs. Adding more than 1 Durian will result in Monster Lasagna. Adding more than 2 twigs will result in Steamed Twigs.\nRecipe[edit | edit source]\n×2\nFillers cannot be Meats or more than 1 extra Inedible.\nCannot have more than 1.0 Monster Food.\nExamples[edit | edit source]\n×2\n×2\n×2\n×2\nNote that this doesn't produce Stuffed Eggplant, because Fancy Spiralled Tubers have higher priority.\nTips[edit | edit source]\nIf made with two twigs and a food item that has 12.5 hunger value or less, this dish will provide a small gain in hunger, sanity and perish time over its components. Keep in mind that it lacks the healing of a cooked potato, however.\nTrivia[edit | edit source]\nFancy Spiralled Tubers were added to Don't Starve Together in Warly's Character Update.\nBy TypeBy Crock Pot Value\nView or edit this template\nFood and Edible Items (by Food Type)\nVeggie\nSeeds\nMeat\nGoodies\nGeneric\nHorrible\nRoughage\nElementals\nBurnt\nRaw\nGears\nGold Dust\nBerry\nWood\nNitre\nLunar Shards\nView or edit this template\nFood and Edible Items (by Food Value)\nMeats\nFishes\nVegetables\nFruits\nMonster Food\nEggs\nDairy\nSweetener\nFrozen\nInedibles\nMagic\nFat\nSeed\nJellyfish\nBone\nFilter\nAntihistamine\nDecoration\nBug\nNo Value Food",
