  "wikitext": "{{Exclusivity|Don't Starve Together}}\n{{Object Infobox\n|icon = {{FULLPAGENAME}}.png\n|image = {{FULLPAGENAME}} Dropped.png\n|foodType = [[Veggie]] [[File:Veggie.png|32px|link=Veggie]]\n|foodRecipe ={{Pic|32px|Potatoes}}x1 {{Pic|32px|Twigs}}x1 {{Pic|32px|Filler}}x2\n|canBeBurned=1\n|hpRestored     = 3\n|hungerRestored = 37.5\n|sanityRestored = 15\n|cooktime       = 15 sec\n|priority       = 10\n|spoil          = 10 Days\n|stack          = 40\n|spawnCode      = \"potatotornado\"\n}}\n{{Quotes\n|wilson = Potato, scientifically infused with the power of a tornado!\n|willow = Woah, I didn't know potatoes came in that shape!\n|wolfgang = Wolfgang loves potato.\n|wendy = Spiralling, just like my life.\n|wx78 = HIGH DENSITY FUEL MADE BY MY MINION\n|wickerbottom = How creative!\n|woodie = I'll eat a tater in any form.\n|maxwell = What an odd way to serve potatoes.\n|wigfrid = Blech.\n|webber = Woah! It's cool, AND edible!\n|warly = Junk food can be as enjoyable as anything gourmet.\n|wormwood = Whirly Swirly!\n|winona = Count on Warly's cookin' to always make my day.\n|wortox = I think I remember when I used to eat food. Maybe.\n|wurt = Hee-hee, spinny potato!\n|walter = I usually mash my potatoes.\n|wanda = Time is kind of like a swirly potato.\n|choose = warly\n}}\n'''Fancy Spiralled Tubers''' are [[Vegetable]] [[Food]] [[Items]] exclusive to ''[[Don't Starve Together]]''. They are cooked in the [[Crock Pot]] by combining 1 [[Potato]], [[Twigs]] and two fillers. It takes 15 seconds to cook.\n\nAdding [[Meats]] will result in [[Kabobs]]. Adding more than 1 [[Durian]] will result in [[Monster Lasagna]]. Adding more than 2 twigs will result in [[Steamed Twigs]].\n\n== {{pic|32|Cookbook}} Recipe ==\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Potatoes\n|item2 = Twigs\n|item3 = Filler\n|count3 = 2\n|tool = Crock Pot\n|result = Fancy Spiralled Tubers\n|note = Fillers cannot be [[Meats]] or more than 1 extra [[Inedible]]. <br>Cannot have more than 1.0 [[Monster Food]].\n}}\n\n== Examples ==\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Potatoes\n|item2 = Twigs\n|count2 = 2\n|item3 = Ice\n|tool = Crock Pot\n|result = Fancy Spiralled Tubers\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Potatoes\n|item2 = Twigs\n|count2 = 2\n|item3 = Berries\n|tool = Crock Pot\n|result = Fancy Spiralled Tubers\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Potatoes\n|item2 = Twigs\n|item3 = Ripe Stone Fruit\n|tool = Crock Pot\n|result = Fancy Spiralled Tubers\n|item4=Ripe Stone Fruit}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Potatoes\n|item2 = Twigs\n|item3 = Honey\n|tool = Crock Pot\n|result = Fancy Spiralled Tubers\n|item4=Honey}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Potatoes\n|item2 = Twigs\n|item3 = Red Cap\n|count3 = 2\n|tool = Crock Pot\n|result = Fancy Spiralled Tubers\n}}\n{{Recipe\n|item1 = Eggplant\n|item2 = Potatoes\n|item3 = Twigs\n|count3 = 2\n|tool = Crock Pot\n|result = Fancy Spiralled Tubers\n|note = Note that this doesn't produce [[Stuffed Eggplant]], because Fancy Spiralled Tubers have higher priority.\n}}\n\n== {{pic32|Prototype}} Tips ==\n\n* If made with two twigs and a food item that has 12.5 hunger value or less, this dish will provide a small gain in hunger, sanity and perish time over its components. Keep in mind that it lacks the healing of a cooked potato, however.\n\n== {{Pic32|Placeholder}} Trivia ==\n\n* Fancy Spiralled Tubers were added to ''Don't Starve Together'' in Warly's [[Don't Starve Together/Version History#July 25, 2019 - Warly Character Update|Character Update]].\n\n{{Crock Pot Food}}\n__NOTOC__\n\n[[vi:Khoai Tây Xiên]]\n[[Category:Crock Pot Recipes]]\n[[Category:Perishables]]\n[[Category:Healing]]\n[[Category:Sanity Boost]]\n[[Category:Vegetables]]\n[[Category:Flammable Objects]]"
}
